    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dances that have a ceremonial or ritual function. Characteristic are movements that are continuously repeated that may reflect a form or inducement of worship, prayer, visionary insights, or healing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000303/ANET</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110115/Anet, working group AAT</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dansen die een ceremoniële of rituele functie hebben. Kenmerkend zijn de eenvoudige bewegingen die continue worden herhaald. Hierdoor hoeft men niet meer na te denken over de bewegingen zelf, waardoor er ruimte is voor interne verkenning in de vorm van aanbidding, gebed, visionaire inzichten, heling en (zelf)bekrachtiging.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
